==Gaya==

===Etymology===
This the only certain term in Gaya. According to {{jpx-ref|Beckwith (2004) p. 40}}, potentially related to {{cog|jpx-pro|*to}} / {{cog|ja|-}} {{ja-r|戸|と|t=door}}, although a bisyllabic/dimoraic reading has also been suggested, in which case this would be in error, and if the intended reading was actually the Sino-Korean reading, this is in severe error.

===Pronunciation===
The transcription 梁 indicates the pronunciation, however the exact reading is uncertain. {{jpx-ref|Beckwith (2004) p. 40}} has more. {{rfp|zra|I don't know anything about the historical pronunciations of Old Korean, someone who does should add an explanation.}}

