===Etymology 1===
{{ja-kanjitab|うつばり|yomi=k}}
From {{inh|ja|ojp|梁|tr=utupari|sort=うつばり}}; attested phonetically in Old Japanese in the ''{{w|Shin'yaku Kegonkyō Ongi Shiki}}'' of 794, with the spelling {{lang|ja|宇都波利}}.<ref name="JDButupari">{{R:JDB|page=124}}</ref><ref name="KDJ2Outubari"/>

Likely a compound of {{com|ja|内|tr1=utsu-|t1=[[inside]]|pos1=bound form|張り|tr2=hari|pos2=the {{m|ja|連用形|tr=ren'yōkei|t=continuative or stem form}} of {{m|ja|張る|tr=haru|t=to [[stick]]; to [[spread]]}}|sort=うつばり}}, as suggested by various works.<ref name="KDJ2Outubari"/>

Alternatively, the initial ''utsu-'' is connected to ''utsu-'', spelled variously in addition to {{m|ja|内|t=inside}} as {{m|ja|全|t=all of which is contained in a group}}, {{m|ja|空}}, {{m|ja|虚|t=an inner hollow or empty space; an inner void}}, which are likely cognates.<ref name="KDJ2Outubari"/>

====Pronunciation====
{{ja-pron|うつばり|acc=0|acc_ref=<ref name="KDJ2Outubari">{{R:Nihon Kokugo Daijiten 2 Online|うつ‐ばり 【梁】|lid=2002006a8faf4RP34cly|kotobank=梁}}
</br>
The {{m|ja|語源説|tr=gogensetsu|t=etymological theory}} section gives the following theories:</br>
# ウチバリ（内張）の転〔名語記・桑家漢語抄所引秘授抄・和句解・日本釈名・東雅・万葉集類林・家屋雑考・大言海〕。
# ウツハリ（全張）の義〔名言通・和訓栞〕。
# ウツハリ（空張）の義〔言元梯〕。ウツハリギ（空張木）の下略〔日本語原学＝林甕臣〕。
</ref>,DJR,NHK
}}

