===Etymology 3===
{{ja-kanjitab|やな|yomi=k|alt=簗}}
From {{inh|ja|ojp|梁|tr=yana|sort=やな}}. Attested in the ''{{w|Nihon Shoki}}'' of 720.<ref name="JDByana">{{R:JDB|page=764}}</ref><ref name="KDJ2Oyana"/>

There are various theories, such as a derivation from {{m|ja|屋魚|tr=ya na|t=house of a fish}}, {{m|ja|やる魚|tr=yaru na|t=a fish to be done}}, an abbreviation of {{m|ja|梁簀|tr=yanasu}}, and a shift from {{m|ja|板庭|tr=itaniwa}}.<ref name="KDJ2Oyana"/>

